Loading data files… I have removed christmas day from data. I have filled missing values of variable event_type_1, event_type_2, event_name_1 and event_name_2 with ‘No Event’ string. This is for sales per department (7)

Model consideration: 1. Arimax 2. Arima + Fourier 3. Arfima

for (i in dept.ids){
    print(i)
    df         <- data.frame(data[data$dept_id == i,])
    EventName1  <- model.matrix(~as.factor(df$event_name_1))[,-1]
    EventName2  <- model.matrix(~as.factor(df$event_name_2))[,-1]
    test_len    <- nrow(df) - 27
    train       <- df[1: test_len, ]
    test        <- df[test_len:nrow(df), ]
    train.ts    <- ts(train$sales, frequency = 7)
    test.ts     <- ts(test$sales, frequency = 7)
    
    xreg.train  <- cbind(
                  MedianPrice = train[,"sell_price_median"],
                  IsWeekday   = train[,"Is_weekday"],
                  snap_CA     = train[,"snap_CA"],
                  snap_TX     = train[,"snap_TX"],
                  snap_WI     = train[,"snap_WI"],
                  event.name1 = EventName1[1: test_len, ],
                  event.name2 = EventName2[1: test_len, ]
                   )
                 
    model.arima <- auto.arima(train.ts, seasonal=TRUE, xreg=xreg.train)
  checkresiduals(model.arima)
  
   xreg.test <- cbind(
                  MedianPrice = test[,"sell_price_median"],
                  IsWeekday   = test[,"Is_weekday"],
                  snap_CA     = test[,"snap_CA"],
                  snap_TX     = test[,"snap_TX"],
                  snap_WI     = test[,"snap_WI"],
                  event.name1 = EventName1[test_len:nrow(df), ],
                  event.name2 = EventName2[test_len:nrow(df), ]
                  )
  forecast.arima <- forecast(model.arima, xreg = xreg.test, h=28)
  print(accuracy(forecast.arima, test$sales))
  }

Here I am combining fourier terms with ARIMA errors per department

for (i in dept.ids){
    print(i)
    df         <- data.frame(data[data$dept_id == i,])
    test_len    <- nrow(df) - 27
    train       <- df[1: test_len, ]
    test        <- df[test_len:nrow(df), ]
    train.ts    <- ts(train$sales, frequency = 7)
    test.ts     <- ts(test$sales, frequency = 7)
    
    xreg.train  <- fourier(train.ts, K=3)
                 
    model.arima <- auto.arima(train.ts, seasonal=FALSE, xreg=xreg.train)
    checkresiduals(model.arima)
  
    xreg.test      <- fourier(test.ts, K=3, h=28)
    forecast.arima <- forecast(model.arima, xreg = xreg.test, h=28)
    print(accuracy(forecast.arima, test$sales))
  }
